	<summary>
	9/29/1994--Introduced.
Amends the Immigration and Nationality Act to expand the definition of &quot;aggravated felony.&quot; Provides for the expedited deportation of aliens convicted of aggravated felonies. Authorizes U.S. district courts, upon the Attorney General's request, to issue a deportation order at such an alien's sentencing. Restricts certain deportation defenses. Directs the Attorney General to operate a criminal tracking center. Extends the visa waiver pilot program and creates a probationary status under such program.

	</summary>
